The paper deals with motion planning for automated vehicles, which is a topic that falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The approach proposed in the paper involves the use of a deep convolutional neural network (CNN) to predict future ego-vehicle poses, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of optimization algorithms, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of motion planning in complex environments, which is a topic that could fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
